description: A file containing documents relating to a conference of British ambassadors in the Soviet Union and Eastern Europe, held in London in November 1975. Documents in the file include the timetable for the conference; records of the discussions at the conference sessions; a draft of a speech at the conference by the Foreign Secretary, James Callaghan; and reports from the British ambassadors in six East European countries on the situation after the Conference on Security and Cooperation in Europe (C.S.C.E.). Other documents in the file include a discussion paper on Western Europe after the C.S.C.E.; a report from the British ambassador in Belgrade, Dugald Stewart, on what might happen in Yugoslavia following the death of the president, Josip Broz Tito; and draft papers on military détente, the Strategic Arms Limitation Talks (SALT), the aftermath of the C.S.C.E., and probable Soviet policies towards Eastern Europe.
